    <initializer>template&lt;class T&gt;
concept <ref refid="concepthelios_1_1engine_1_1common_1_1concepts_1_1IsSystemLike" kindref="compound">helios::engine::common::concepts::IsSystemLike</ref> =  requires(T&amp; t, <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1UpdateContext" kindref="compound">helios::engine::runtime::world::UpdateContext</ref>&amp; updateContext) {
        {t.update(updateContext) } -&gt; std::same_as&lt;void&gt;;
    } &amp;&amp; HasTag&lt;T, <ref refid="structhelios_1_1engine_1_1common_1_1tags_1_1SystemRole" kindref="compound">tags::SystemRole</ref>&gt;    </initializer>
    <briefdescription>
<para>Constrains T to types that provide `update(UpdateContext&amp;)` and declare `EngineRoleTag = SystemRole`. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A type satisfies IsSystemLike if it: 1. Provides a `void update(UpdateContext&amp;)` method for per-frame logic. 2. Declares `using EngineRoleTag = SystemRole;` to explicitly opt in.</para>
<para>Used by `SystemRegistry::add&lt;T&gt;()` to gate registration.</para>
